department: Art of Africa and the Americas
description:
Horus eye Blue; inlays of red jasper, lapis lazuli, obsidian and alabaster, or of glass imitating these stone on one side only; reverse plain; one ring or edge for suspension; represents the left eye, the eye of the sun god Ra
Udjat: Eye of Horus (Eye of Aah); blue faience with inlays of red jasper, lapis lazuli, obsidian and alabaster
title: Udjat Eye of Aah
